text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia auricoma, commonly known as Petermann wattle and Alumaru, is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Northern Territory and the eastern Goldfields region of Western Australia.The erect sparsely branched shrub typically grows to a height of 2.5 metres (8 ft) and produces yellow flowers.
